President Obama will host Prime Minister Singh of India for an official state visit at the White House on November 24. This visit will emphasize the strong partnership between the United States and India and the friendship between the American and Indian people. The two leaders will discuss various global, regional, and bilateral issues of shared interest, as well as review the progress made in the strategic dialogue launched in July. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama will also host Prime Minister Singh and his wife for an official state dinner. The goal of the visit is to strengthen and enhance the partnership between the two nations for the benefit of their people and the world.